<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-06-30T02:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-06-30T02:35:00-05:00" n="474" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d474">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/375: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kornfeld</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-06-30T11:00:00+03:25"><hi rend="italic">June 30,
                                        1924—11 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 3
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>46. Sinclair representative here has been asked by Persian Government to
                            give written engagement to defend rights under concession as against any
                            claims based on grant by Imperial firman to Sepahsalar which was
                            afterwards transferred to Khoshtaria, and to waive claim of any sort
                            upon the Persian Government should an adverse judgment disallow
                            Sinclair’s title.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kornfeld</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>